main event: A civilian observer reported seeing a bright, stationary, saucer-like craft performing intelligently controlled maneuvers over King of Prussia, PA on June 10, 1966.
interesting points: The object was exceptionally bright and appeared for around 30 seconds.
The observer stated the object performed 'intelligently controlled' maneuvers.
The object was described as a bright light, larger than the head of a match held at arm's length.
The observer estimated the object's speed to be around 1,000 mph.
The observer was driving south at 65 mph when they saw the object.
